<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057071-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 4 and c = 9. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.1</li><li>26.4</li><li>63.6</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}={16}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}-{16}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{65}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{65}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.0622577482985}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.1}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{26.387799961215}\approx{26.4}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{63.612200038785}\approx{63.6}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>